      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum nonlinear FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening material model justified by literature and material coupon data; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation.",
      "rationale": "Continuum FEA with nonlinear geometry and bilinear isotropic hardening (Ti-6Al-4V: E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, Et=1.14 GPa) is standard for metallic implant simulation. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and block modeled with augmented Lagrangian. Model form appropriate for compression-bending regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of test specimens; uncertainty in inputs quantified.",
      "rationale": "Geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of 11 test specimens (dimensional tolerance ±0.01 mm). Material properties from certified mill test reports for Ti-6Al-4V bar stock. Uncertainty in elastic modulus (±5%) and yield strength (±3%) propagated through sensitivity analysis. Input uncertainty contribution to QoI uncertainty quantified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lot; traceability to material certificates established; specimen dimensions measured and reported.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lot with full material traceability. Specimens measured by CMM prior to testing. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 guidance for this risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two distinct load configurations or environmental conditions to bound model applicability.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration only. No torsion, tension, or cyclic loading conditions included in this validation activity. Achieved level (1) falls below required level (2); this shortfall is noted and accepted given that the COU is explicitly scoped to static compression-bending per ASTM F1717."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate experimental test fixture geometry and load application within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Experimental fixture geometry (ASTM F1717 UHMWPE blocks, 35 mm pedicle screw spacing, actuator load point) reproduced in FEA to within 0.5 mm. Load application rate (5 mm/min quasi-static) treated as rate-independent in FEA, justified by absence of rate sensitivity in Ti-6Al-4V at room temperature. Input parameter equivalency confirmed by cross-laboratory comparison."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval <1.96 for all QoIs; percentage difference <10%.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: mean %diff 4.2%, E/uval 0.87. Yield force: mean %diff 6.8%, E/uval 1.42. Force at 40 mm: mean %diff 7.5%, E/uval 1.61. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Comparison performed across N=11 specimens and two laboratories with consistent results."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are clinically and regulatorily relevant for pedicle screw construct performance assessment.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterize structural performance relevant to clinical failure modes (permanent deformation, fracture)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
